{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":198614,"duration_api_ms":250570,"num_turns":24,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"d0644c8c-9e80-4a27-9a59-e357c4e0336d","total_cost_usd":0.9602606499999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":4924,"cache_creation_input_tokens":49666,"cache_read_input_tokens":583281,"output_tokens":3953,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":49666,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":4924,"outputTokens":3953,"cacheReadInputTokens":583281,"cacheCreationInputTokens":49666,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.725498,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":143,"outputTokens":16821,"cacheReadInputTokens":560984,"cacheCreationInputTokens":75533,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.23476265000000004,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"Issue 3 fix deviates from spec: The spec says 'Auto-populate plan_hash from the milestone snapshot' for new rows when caller's plan_hash is None, and backfill existing open entries from the snapshot. The implementation does the OPPOSITE — it explicitly removes auto-population (line 3039: `let effective_plan_hash = plan_hash.map(str::to_owned)`) and only records `snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation` as provenance metadata. The `safe_plan_hash_backfill` method only fills plan_hash on existing open entries during replay when the snapshot hash hasn't changed, but never on initial creation. The spec's acceptance criterion 'Lineage entries auto-populate plan_hash from the milestone snapshot when callers omit it' is NOT met. The diff comments justify this as 'the snapshot read races with persist_plan()' — this is a valid concern but the spec explicitly accepted this trade-off and required auto-population. Either the spec needs to be amended to match the conservative provenance-only approach, or the code needs to auto-populate plan_hash on new row creation as the spec requires.","rationale":"The spec for Issue 3 is explicit: 'New rows: When creating a new TaskRunEntry and the caller's plan_hash is None, read it from the snapshot.' The diff removes exactly this behavior (previously present) and replaces it with provenance-only tracking. This directly contradicts the acceptance criteria. The test assertions were also changed from expecting auto-population to expecting None, confirming the implementation intentionally diverges from the spec."},{"body":"Issue 1 (duplicate journal detail structs) was NOT addressed in this diff. The `StartJournalDetails` and `CompletionJournalDetails` structs are defined only in model.rs (lines 374 and 405) and reused in fs.rs via imports (line 25-27). However, checking the code more carefully, this was apparently already resolved in a prior round — the structs in model.rs are public with both Serialize and Deserialize, and fs.rs imports and uses them directly with `impl StartJournalDetails` blocks adding parse/merge/render methods. The spec says 'eliminate the duplicate structs entirely' — this appears to already be done. No action needed, but the diff being reviewed doesn't show this fix, meaning it was either already in place or addressed in a different commit. Verify the diff scope covers all three issues.","rationale":"The diff only modifies 3 files with changes focused on Issues 2 and 3 (plan_hash handling). Issue 1's structural fix (eliminating duplicate journal detail structs) is either pre-existing or was done in earlier rounds. The reviewer should confirm that Issue 1 was previously completed and doesn't need changes in this round."}],"summary":"Reviewed the diff across fs.rs, model.rs, and service.rs (3 files, +144/-62 lines). All 683 tests pass. The changes address: (1) removing auto-population of plan_hash on new TaskRunEntry creation in favor of provenance-only tracking via snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation, (2) making the None-provenance backfill path conservative (skip instead of adopting current snapshot), (3) adding a tracing::warn for the contract violation in unique_terminal_replay_match, (4) new test coverage for merge_attempt_entries, and (5) updated test assertions to match the new non-auto-population behavior. The runless-to-named completion path (Issue 2) correctly handles started_at disambiguation and the debug_assert guards have been replaced with runtime checks. However, the plan_hash changes (Issue 3) directly contradict the spec's requirement to auto-populate plan_hash from the snapshot on new rows — the code instead records only provenance metadata and never fills plan_hash from the snapshot on creation. Issue 1 (journal detail struct duplication) does not appear in this diff and was presumably addressed in a prior round."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"744736d0-f98a-47d0-8451-012180b6e7cd"}
